episodes.title: The Banishment of Andrew
episodes.description: In this week’s episode, we delve into the King's decisive move regarding his brother, Prince Andrew - stripping him of his remaining styles, titles, and honours, and declaring that he will now be known simply as Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor. We explore what this means for his future, his ex-wife's Sarah Ferguson, the late Queen's corgis, and how their daughters, Beatrice and Eugenie, have been putting on a brave face while abroad. Plus, we look ahead to Prince William's Earthshot Prize event in Rio and unpack the Sussexes' latest revelations from across the Atlantic. Learn more about your ad choices.
